Alpaca Festival Sheffield
Description: "The festival of Algorithmic Patterns in the Creative Arts. If you are curious about strange patterns in different forms then this one is for you! There'll be a top notch algorave with people writing code to make electronic dance music
URL: also a concert with pattern-based instrumental music and closing party that'll be a blend of the two. There will also be loads of talks about different kinds of strange patterns. We'll announce the hands-on workshops soon too - ~10 different workshops to choose from around patterns in juggling
Longitude: music etc. A mix of heritage/craft workshops and more tech-infused ones. It'll be a bit unfashionable in having little or no AI stuff. Any algorithms involved will be wholesomely handmade by humans
column10: whether ancient procedures from craft/music practice or live coding/algorave. There'll also be an online conference running through the event and into the following weekend
column11: with watch parties in Berlin and Sheffield."

Name: Rutherford Appleton Laboratory: Public Access Day
URL: we are delighted to be able to run an access day at the laboratory - giving people and families the chance to see and experience science up close
Latitude: from the smallest building blocks of our universe
Longitude: right up to the vast scales of space.  There will be a morning (09:30-12:00) and an afternoon session (14:00-16:30)
column10: with interactive workshops and hands-on activities for those with younger children
column11: and tours and talks for older groups. All sessions will start with a short introduction to the lab. Please only book on the morning or afternoon session. After selecting your tickets
column12: you'll be able to choose which tour
column14: you'd like to attend - although please do note that as a working lab we do occasionally have to change our schedules at the last minute.  We're really looking forward to welcoming you to the lab! If you can't make it in person
column16: where we'll be streaming our talks (and live links to CERN
column17: home to the largest experiment in the world!) live."

Name: Barcamp Surrey
Description: "A Technology 'Open Forum' in the Heart of Surrey. Everyone is encouraged to attend—whether to simply listen or to actively participate by giving a talk. Talks can cover any topic you think others might find interesting
Longitude: or even a technical or non-technical subject. It’s all about fostering curiosity and community engagement!"
